The way this commit works is it places a code under try block to check whether 2 step verification is active. If yes then it exits the program without any error and with a message to the user to deactivate 2 step verification before running the code. If 2 step verification id not active then it raises an exception which means we are good to go and thus the exception is passed,then finally block is executed to do the task the code is intended to do.

Remove max num (#64)

* Adding new buttons

* Added Feature Browse
Now You can browse different results for the same query
Pressing the => button will download another image for the current query
Pressing the <= button will take you back to previous image.
The max number of images that will be downloaded per query is 3 but it can be changed using the max_num flag
After three images it will cycle back to first image.
Images are downloaded only when user asks for them. You dont pay for what you dont use.

* Removed unnecessary instance variable  self.current_image

* Removed Redundant option max_num
You can now download as many images as you want and since they are downloaded on demand,
a maximum limit on the number of images is redundant
